{"title":"DVO Diamond Shines with Bigger 36mm Stanchions, Lighter Air Spring","link":"https://bikerumor.com/dvo-diamond-shines-with-bigger-36mm-stanchions-lighter-air-spring/","date":1709947516000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-2.jpg\" alt=\"2024 dvo diamond trail enduro mountain bike suspension fork\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-2.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-2-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-2-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-2-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-2-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-2-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Following a similar path as the longer travel Onyx did in 2023 by jumping to 38mm stanchions, the DVO Diamond is moving to 36mm stanchions, up from 35mm, and switches to their SL Air Spring.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Conveniently, the new Diamond gets the Onyx’s prior lowers since that fork used to have 36mm sliders, but the rest of its chassis and some internals are new.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-4.jpg\"><img width=\"1800\" height=\"1350\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-4.jpg\" alt=\"closeup on crown of 2024 dvo diamond trail enduro mountain bike suspension fork\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-4.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-4-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-4-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-4-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-4-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-4-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Starting at the top, it gets a new, lighter crown. Inside, it gets the new SL Air Spring with self-equalizing chamber. DVO’s prior OTT (Off The Top) allowed for independent adjustment of the positive and negative chambers, but unless you really spent the time to fiddle with it, they found many users weren’t taking full advantage of that system.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The SL Air Spring uses a simple transfer port to automatically fill both positive and negative chambers simultaneously and equally, just like most other air forks on the market. You lose a bit of the customization opportunity, but it drops up to 150g, too.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-3.jpg\"><img width=\"1800\" height=\"1350\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-3.jpg\" alt=\"closeup on dropouts of 2024 dvo diamond trail enduro mountain bike suspension fork\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-3.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-3-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-3-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-3-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-3-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-3-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This move also starts to simplify their fork travel hierarchy. The Onyx will have 160-180mm travel, internally adjustable in 10mm increments. The Diamond does the same, but with 140-160mm travel (so, no more 170mm option). We’re betting the Sapphire will only be 120-140mm, soon.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-1.jpg\"><img width=\"1800\" height=\"1350\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-1.jpg\" alt=\"closeup on lowers of 2024 dvo diamond trail enduro mountain bike suspension fork\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-1.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-1-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-1-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-1-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-1-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/2024-DVO-Diamond-36mm-stanchion-enduro-trail-MTB-fork-1-1536x1152.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This lets them optimize the stanchion length for a given category rather than have to carry extra weight for longer stanchions just to accommodate a higher travel range.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Look for this new DVO Diamond to hit the market a little later this year. Weight is TBA, we’ll update when we get final specs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://dvosuspension.com\" target=\"_blank\">DVOsuspension.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/dvo-diamond-shines-with-bigger-36mm-stanchions-lighter-air-spring/\">DVO Diamond Shines with Bigger 36mm Stanchions, Lighter Air Spring</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"7919f9c8106a8ab84f2150e3293667bff2802658bfaf903b872846ec79643f74","category":"Cycling"}